---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = '2026-03-31';
---
<Layout title="PollenPal - Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for PollenPal iOS app.">
  <div class="pt-24 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
      <a href="/en/apps/pollenpal" class="text-sm text-text-muted hover:text-accent-purple transition-colors">&larr; PollenPal</a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2 text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted mb-8">PollenPal - Pollen Forecast</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted">
        <p>OpenClaw ("we", "us", "our") built PollenPal as a free application. This page is used to inform users regarding our policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Information Collection and Use</h2>
        <p>PollenPal does not collect or store personal data on external servers. The app processes data locally on your device.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>No personal information is collected or transmitted</li>
          <li>No usage analytics or tracking</li>
          <li>No third-party analytics services</li>
          <li>No advertising identifiers</li>
          <li>No account or registration required</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Location Data</h2>
        <p>PollenPal may request access to your device's location to provide local pollen forecasts. Location data is:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Used only to fetch pollen data from weather APIs for your area</li>
          <li>Not stored on any server</li>
          <li>Not shared with any third party</li>
          <li>Not used for tracking or profiling</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can use the app without granting location access by entering your city manually.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
        <p>All allergen profiles, symptom logs, and preferences are stored locally on your device using UserDefaults and on-device storage. This data never leaves your device.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>PollenPal uses the Open-Meteo API to fetch pollen forecast data. Only your approximate location (city-level coordinates) is sent to retrieve weather data. No personal identifiers are transmitted. Open-Meteo is a free, open-source weather API. See <a href="https://open-meteo.com/en/terms" class="text-accent-purple hover:underline" target="_blank">Open-Meteo Terms</a>.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>PollenPal does not collect any personal information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:magic4e@gmail.com" class="text-accent-purple hover:underline">magic4e@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
